What about indenting to the arrow? Like this:
```php
$somethingBuilder->addDescription('Hello')
                 ->addNumber(42)
                 ->addSomethingElse('something else');
```
Doctrine does that in their [docs](http://docs.doctrine-project.org/projects/doctrine-orm/en/latest/reference/query-builder.html#binding-parameters-to-your-query).

Also an option if the first chaining should be in the line with the variable or in the next one would be useful.

